name: Night at the Station
description:
"One of the most interesting things about graffiti on US railroads is the accompanying subculture which has developed along with it, which often differs from the other forms seen on urban transit systems or in cities. 

In cities, graffitiing the subway was a part of a wider practice which also incorporated street level tagging on buildings, bridges, and on the infrastructure related to the subway system. In contrast, freight train writers tend to stick solely to freight cars and won’t tag other places."
